# Testing

## Framework

- **Vitest** with jsdom environment
- **@testing-library/react** for component tests
- Setup file: `setupTests.ts` (root)

## Running tests

- `yarn test:app` — run tests in watch mode
- `yarn test:all` — full suite (typecheck + code + other + app)
- `yarn test:coverage` — coverage report

## Coverage thresholds

- Lines: 60%, Branches: 70%, Functions: 63%, Statements: 60%
- Do not lower these thresholds.

## Conventions

- Tests are **colocated** next to source files (e.g., `foo.test.ts` beside `foo.ts`)
- Fixture-heavy tests go in dedicated `tests/` directories
- Use existing test helpers from `packages/excalidraw/tests/helpers/`:
  - `render()` for component rendering
  - `API.createElement()` for element creation
  - `assertElements()` for element assertions
- Always write tests for new features and bug fixes
- Prefer integration-style tests that exercise real component behavior over shallow mocks

## How to verify

- Run `yarn test:app --watch=false` — all tests must pass.
- Run `yarn test:coverage` — verify thresholds are not lowered (lines 60%, branches 70%, functions 63%, statements 60%).
- Check that new/changed source files have corresponding `.test.ts(x)` files.
- Verify test helpers are reused: search for `render(`, `API.createElement(`, `assertElements(` in new test files.
